    • Constructor Detail

      • PrintSetUpDialogue

        public PrintSetUpDialogue(FrameManager manager,
                  java.lang.String caseNum,
                  java.util.ArrayList<CaseIcon> selectedIcons)
        Populates this dialogue with all of the necessary graphical components. Handles backend retrieval of printer information.
        Parameters:
        manager - the instance of FrameManager that initialized this dialogue
        caseNum - the number of the case that the images are being printed from
        selectedIcons - ArrayList of CaseIcon objects representing the images to be printed
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any parameters are null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the selectedIcons ArrayList is empty

    • Method Detail

      • actionPerformed

        public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent e)
        Mandatory method required in all classes that implement ActionListener.

        Below is a list of possible source objects and their corresponding actions:

        • fullPageButton
          • Changes the selected print layout format to full page, without header.
        • oneImgButton
          • Changes the selected print layout format to one image per page, with header.
        • twoImgButton
          • Changes the selected print layout format to two images per page, with header.
        • fourImgButton
          • Changes the selected print layout format to four images per page, with header.
        • eightImgButton
          • Changes the selected print layout format to eight images per page, with header.
        • printButton
          • Calls the initiatePrint method; displays an error dialogue if the print job failed to complete, closes this window otherwise.
        Specified by:
        actionPerformed in interface java.awt.event.ActionListener

      • generatePDF

        private void generatePDF()
                  throws java.io.IOException,
                         InvalidFileException
        Generates a PDF file - formatted in accordance with the user settings specified in this dialogue - that contains all of the selected images, as well as a standardized department header.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if modification of the generated PDF file unexpectedly fails
        InvalidFileException - if the program is unable to locate the logo file for the department header, or if the images cannot be loaded into memory

      • addHeader

        private void addHeader()
                throws java.io.IOException,
                       InvalidFileException

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if modification of the generated PDF file unexpectedly fails
